- The "Proposed Workflow" warning banner is retained (verification is still `unverified`).

### Why

Round R0 shipped a plan with an "uncertain assumptions" block listing four risks instead of resolving them. A NOGO reviewer proved each was a genuine defect: exit `2` collided with argparse AND `gdb_runner.py:380`; the test asserted `payload["status"] == 2` when `emit_json_status` makes `status` the string `"error"` (guaranteed-fail RED); a `" WARNING:"` classifier substring co-occurs with a successful capture's `wrote ` line; and relaxing 4 positionals to `nargs="?"` silently turned a kernel-path typo from a loud error into a no-op. The durable through-line: a plan's own risks block is a TODO list for the next iteration, not a disclaimer — verdict-floor reviewers treat an acknowledged-but-unfixed defect the same as an unacknowledged one.

